<paragraph blockId="2.[109,878,202,1510]" pageId="2" pageNumber="347">
This being the case, Dr. Leidy`s name. in its original form 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1856" box="[115,232,772,792]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Deinodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="2" pageNumber="347" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Deinodon</taxonomicName>
, is not preoccupied and is the proper name to apply to those species which for many years have been arranged 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,874,813,827]" pageId="2" pageNumber="347">under</emphasis>
the generic name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" box="[384,529,839,865]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="2" pageNumber="347" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Aublysodon</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[109,878,202,1510]" pageId="2" pageNumber="347">It may be remarked here that more recently Prof. Cope† has emended also the Dinodon of Duméril and Bibron into Dianodon.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
